			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;   margin-bottom: 10px;  width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;	compositeName.add(&quot;cn=Some\\\\Person6,ou=company1,c=Sweden&quot;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;compositeName.toString()&lt;/tt&gt; now renders &lt;tt&gt;cn=Some\\\Person6,ou=company1,c=Sweden&lt;/tt&gt;, which is, incidentally, not accepted by Sun&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;LdapName&lt;/tt&gt; either.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the end I decided to do the easiest possible thing: since the &lt;tt&gt;CompositeName&lt;/tt&gt; only has one component anyway (I still don&apos;t understand why Sun uses that class for this but, hey - that&apos;s the way it is), instead of &lt;tt&gt;toString()&lt;/tt&gt; I now use &lt;tt&gt;get(0)&lt;/tt&gt; to supply to &lt;tt&gt;DistinguishedName&lt;/tt&gt;. The latter produces the untainted String and we&apos;re all set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I sincerely hope I haven&apos;t broken any other special case here, but all the unit and integration tests still run so I think we&apos;re actually all right.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
